Overview

	vfnmake is a reletively simple Makefile generator. It works on fire-and-forget basis with as least configuration as possible. It does not try to compete with CMake or Autotools. I wrote it because writting Makefiles, while not really difficult, can be really tedious even for the simple projects.



Usage

	./configure.pl [OPTIONS...]
Arguments:
	--name NAME
		Specify the name of the executable file. Default: a.out
	--src DIR
		Specify the directory with the source. Default: src/ or ./
	--objs DIR
		Specify the directory for the *.o files. Default: objs/
	--bin DIR
		Specify the directory for the binary files. Default: ./
	--cc COMMA_SEPARATED_LIST_OF_COMPILERS
		Comma separated list of used C compilers. The first one available is used. Default: clang, gcc
	--cxx COMMA_SEPARATED_LIST_OF_COMPILERS
		Comma separated list of used C++ compilers. The first one available is used. Default: clang++, g++
	--dcc COMPILER
		A compiler for 'make debug'. Default: g++
	-c FLAG, --cflag FLAG		(add)
	-C FLAG, --Cflag FLAG		(remove)
		Add/remove a compilation flag.
	--cflags COMMA_SEPARATED_LIST_OF_FLAGS
		Overwrite the previous cflags.
	-x FLAG, --cxxflag FLAG		(add)
	-X FLAG, --Cxxflag FLAG		(remove)
		Add/remove a C++ compilation flag. These are used only in C++ IN ADDITION to the regular cflags.
	--cflags COMMA_SEPARATED_LIST_OF_FLAGS
		Overwrite the previous cxxflags.
	-On
		Set the optimization to n.
	-l LIBRARY, --lib LIBRARY	(add)
	-L LIBRARY, --Lib LIBRARY	(remove)
		Add/remove a library to link.
	--libs COMMA_SEPARATED_LIST_OF_LIBRARIES
		Overwrite the previous libraries.
	-p, --pkg PACKAGE			(add)
	-P, --Pkg PACKAGE			(remove)
		Add/remove a package for pkg-config.
	--pkgs COMMA_SEPARATED_LIST_OF_PACKAGES
		Overwrite the previous packages.
	-noe, --no-echo
	-e,	  --echo
		Print the executed commands or not. Default: --echo
	--gcc
		Use only gcc/g++.
	--cpp0x
		Use c++0x standard for C++ and switch to gcc/g++.
	-q, --quiet
		Do not print the used config.
	--stdout
		Print the Makefile to the stdout instead of saving in the file so it can be piped directly to make ("./configure.pl --stdout | make -f -").
	--reset
		Set the default compiler lists and directories, turns on echo and disables c++0x mode.



Make targets

	all
		default options
	debug (d)
		compile with -g flag, O0 optimization and DEBUG macro
	clean (c)
		delete all compilation results
	fresh (f)
		force full recompilation (equivalent of 'make clean && make')
	run (r)
		compile and run



Manual vfnmake config file editing

	The file must have the following construction:
	OPTION:
	SOME_SPACES/TABS VALUE(s)
	ANOTHER OPTION:...

	Even if the value would be empty, there must be an empty line. The program will go crazy otherwise.
	To reset an option, delete BOTH of its lines.
	The config file is rewritten on each run so don't bother with formatting it.
